Agent1 Round 1: The term refers to the angle made between the rake face and the radial line. This description matches the definition of **Rake angle** in manufacturing processes, particularly in metal cutting tools. The rake face is the portion of the tool facing forward relative to the direction of chip flow, forming an angle with the radial line (which passes through the vertex of the cutting edge and extends radially outward). Hence, we conclude that option \( \text{B} \):
\boxed{\text{B}}
Answer: B
